    {
      "role": "narrator",
      "content": "A dull ache pulses behind your eyes as consciousness slowly returns. You blink, trying to clear the haze, and find yourself lying on damp, cold earth. Above, a sky of bruised purple and grey presses down, threatening rain. A vast expanse of forest stretches to your southeast, its distant trees a dark, impenetrable wall. To the north, the land rolls into what appears to be farmland, though the details are obscured by the gloom. A faint, low rumble, like a distant beast, echoes from somewhere far off, a sound that vibrates through the very ground beneath you. You push yourself up, your limbs stiff and uncooperative, and a chill wind whips around you, carrying the scent of damp earth and something indefinably wild. Your name, Dam, is the only anchor in this sea of forgotten moments. You are alone, save for a shadowy, unknown figure standing motionless some distance away, partially obscured by the shifting light. How you arrived here, or why, remains a complete mystery. \n\nWhat do you do?",
