  "codexEntries": [
    {
      "id": "9ba9bfbc-2912-4a76-b4c8-61d9f1e1eeca",
      "category": "bestiary",
      "entityId": "cat",
      "title": "The Enigmatic Feline: A Study of the Mysterious Cat",
      "content": "In the vast and varied realms, few creatures have captivated the imagination and curiosity of scholars and adventurers alike as the enigmatic cat. Known for its sleek form and independent nature, the cat is a creature of both beauty and mystery, its true origins and capabilities shrouded in the mists of time.\n\n**Physicality and Biology**\nThe cat is a creature of remarkable agility and grace, its lithe body covered in a coat of fur that varies in color and pattern from one specimen to another. Its eyes, often described as pools of liquid gold or emerald, are said to hold a wisdom that belies its small stature. The cat's biology is as intriguing as its appearance, with some scholars speculating that it possesses a unique ability to heal rapidly from injuries, a trait that has earned it the moniker 'the self-renewing hunter.'\n\n**Ecology and Habitat**\nCats are found in a wide variety of habitats, from the dense forests of Eldoria to the bustling cities of the human realms. They are solitary creatures, preferring to hunt alone and only forming temporary alliances with others of their kind during mating season. Their diet is varied, consisting of small mammals, birds, and even insects, making them a versatile and adaptable predator.\n\n**Myths and Legends**\nThe cat is a creature of many myths and legends. In some cultures, it is revered as a symbol of good fortune and prosperity, while in others, it is feared as a harbinger of misfortune and death. One of the most enduring myths is that of the 'Nine Lives' cat, a creature said to possess the ability to cheat death nine times before finally succumbing to its fate. Whether this is mere folklore or a hint at a deeper truth about the cat's biology remains a subject of much debate among scholars.\n\n**Adventurer's Account**\n'The first time I encountered a cat was in the heart of the Whispering Woods. It was a creature of such grace and beauty that I could not help but be captivated. It moved with a fluidity that was almost hypnotic, its eyes seeming to hold the very essence of the forest itself. I have faced many creatures in my travels, but none have left such a lasting impression as the enigmatic cat.' - Thalion Swiftfoot, Elven Ranger",
      "isNew": true,
      "discoveredAt": 50
    }
  ],
